The spectra of SN~2004ek were obtained at 21, 22, 78 (pre-peak), 103 and 134 (post-peak) days.
 The first two spectra were taken at the epoch of the early cooling phase, and they show a blue continuum where diluted P-Cygni profiles of Balmer lines are barely visible. \ion{Fe}{ii}~$\lambda$5169 and possibly \ion{He}{i}~$\lambda$5875 in absorption are also visible. 
The later spectra  peak in the continuum around 5000--5500~\AA, and show strong broad H$\alpha$ emission with a marginal and narrow  P-Cygni absorption. The other Balmer lines and in particular H$\beta$ show prominent P-Cygni features.
